TITLE: "Push at State Capitol to end subminimum wage for people with disabilities"
AUTHOR: David Schuman
DESCRIPTION: For decades, it's been legal to pay people with disabilities less than minimum wage, but there's momentum building to get rid of the practice.

TITLE: "Minnesota House passes "trans refuge" legislation after late-night debate"
AUTHOR: WCCO Staff
DESCRIPTION: The legislation prohibits enforcing out-of-state subpoenas, arrest warrants and extradition requests for people from other states who sought treatment that is legal in Minnesota. The bill ultimately passed with a 68-62 vote.

TITLE: "Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez Slams Republicans Deeming Rosa Parks Book 'Too Woke'"
DESCRIPTION: Cortez gave an impassioned House floor speech Thursday to rail against GOP efforts to censor, ban and regulate books in public schools.

TITLE: "Disabled Wisconsin voters say absentee law not followed"
AUTHOR: CBS Minnesota
DESCRIPTION: Disabled voters who need assistance submitting absentee ballots say local election leaders across Wisconsin are not following federal law during early voting in the high-stakes state Supreme Court race.

TITLE: "India’s ruling party just kicked a major rival out of Parliament — and sparked a new crisis"
AUTHOR: Zack Beauchamp

TITLE: "Michigan Repeals ‘Right-To-Work’ Law In Historic Win For Unions"
DESCRIPTION: Gov. Gretchen Whitmer also signed a bill restoring the state’s “prevailing wage” law to boost pay on government-funded projects.

TITLE: "Judge Rejects Trump’s Claims Of Executive Power, Orders Aides To Testify In Jan. 6 Probe"
DESCRIPTION: Mark Meadows, Stephen Miller and others must testify in a criminal investigation into Trump's efforts to overturn the 2020 election, the judge said.

TITLE: "House passes GOP bill that would give parents more influence over schools"
AUTHOR: CBS Minnesota
DESCRIPTION: Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer promised the legislation faces a "dead end" in the Senate.

TITLE: "House Republicans Visit Jan. 6 Rioters At D.C. Jail"
DESCRIPTION: Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene (R-Ga.) led a delegation of House members to inspect the alleged mistreatment of Trump supporters connected to Jan. 6, 2021.

TITLE: "Will 'educational freedom' handcuff Texas' public schools?"
DESCRIPTION: SB 8 would provide thousands of taxpayer dollars for families to change schools. Critics wonder where the money is coming from — and whether it helps Texas students.
